                            <comment id="16122384" author="rohini" created="Thu, 10 Aug 2017 21:39:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It should be build/ivy/lib/Pig/jython-standalone-2.7.1.jar&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16122401" author="dbist13" created="Thu, 10 Aug 2017 21:50:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=rohini&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;rohini&quot;&gt;rohini&lt;/a&gt; it is jython-standalone, eventhough ivy says jython.version, with my patch, this is what I see in the directory&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;hw12107:pig aervits$ ls build/ivy/lib/Pig/jython*
build/ivy/lib/Pig/jython-standalone-2.7.1.jar
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;based on this &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/pig/blob/trunk/ivy.xml#L244&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/pig/blob/trunk/ivy.xml#L244&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16122478" author="rohini" created="Thu, 10 Aug 2017 22:52:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That is what I meant&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;classpathentry exported=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;&quot;&lt;/span&gt; kind=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;lib&quot;&lt;/span&gt; path=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;build/ivy/lib/Pig/jython-2.7.1.jar&quot;&lt;/span&gt;/&amp;gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;should be&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;classpathentry exported=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;&quot;&lt;/span&gt; kind=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;lib&quot;&lt;/span&gt; path=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;build/ivy/lib/Pig/jython-standalone-2.7.1.jar&quot;&lt;/span&gt;/&amp;gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;in the patch&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16122488" author="dbist13" created="Thu, 10 Aug 2017 22:57:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=rohini&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;rohini&quot;&gt;rohini&lt;/a&gt; I amended the patch, though I must say that file is out of date as it also references hadoop 0.20 etc.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16122779" author="rohini" created="Fri, 11 Aug 2017 03:31:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1. Committed to trunk. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I guess the file has not been updated in a while. We have to fix it sometime to work with newer versions of hadoop and add Tez and Spark. Instead of having a hardcoded file that will go outdated often as versions are incremented would be better to have a ant target that generates the file based on dependencies in build/ivy/lib. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
